<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1473,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1725,1750]" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gressitt" authorityYear="1942" box="[321,501,1725,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cassida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juglans">
<emphasis box="[321,501,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">Cassida juglans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remained since its description rather enigmatic as 
<bibRefCitation author="Gressitt, J. L." box="[1067,1235,1725,1750]" journalOrPublisher="Lignan Natural History Survey and Museum Special Publication" pageId="7" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 4" part="5" refString="Gressitt, J. L. (1942) New tortoise beetles from China (Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Lignan Natural History Survey and Museum Special Publication, 5, 1 - 4." title="New tortoise beetles from China (Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae)" type="journal article" year="1942">Gressitt (1942)</bibRefCitation>
compared it to 
<taxonomicName authority="Boheman, 1854" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cassida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigriventris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">C. nigriventris</emphasis>
Boheman, 1854
</taxonomicName>
, probably mainly because of combination of uniformly pale yellow dorsum and black ventral side, and later transferred the species to subgenus 
<emphasis box="[795,888,1798,1821]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">Taiwana</emphasis>
Spaeth, 1913 (
<bibRefCitation author="Gressitt, J. L." box="[1058,1213,1797,1822]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences" pageId="7" pageNumber="57" pagination="433 - 592" part="27" refString="Gressitt, J. L. (1952) The tortoise beetles of China (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 27, 433 - 592, pls 1 - 36." title="The tortoise beetles of China (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae)" type="journal article" year="1952">Gressitt 1952</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen, S. &amp; Yu, P. &amp; Sun, C. &amp; Tʼan, C. &amp; Zia, Y." bookContentInfo="653 pp." box="[1233,1436,1797,1822]" journalOrPublisher="Science Press, Beijing, xv" pageId="7" pageNumber="57" refString="Chen, S., Yu, P., Sun, C., Tʼan, C. &amp; Zia, Y. (1986) Fauna Sinica. Insecta. Coleoptera Hispidae. Science Press, Beijing, xv + 653 pp. + 15 pls." title="Fauna Sinica. Insecta. Coleoptera Hispidae" type="book" year="1986">
Chen 
<emphasis box="[1299,1355,1797,1822]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">et al.</emphasis>
(1986)
</bibRefCitation>
probably merely followed the original description as they retained 
<taxonomicName authority="in Taiwana" authorityName="in Taiwana" box="[904,1154,1833,1858]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cassida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juglans">
<emphasis box="[904,1021,1833,1858]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">C. juglans</emphasis>
in 
<emphasis box="[1058,1154,1834,1857]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">Taiwana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
while the 
<typeStatus box="[1273,1371,1833,1858]" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">holotype</typeStatus>
lacks features typical for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1913" box="[373,476,1870,1893]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Taiwania" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[373,476,1870,1893]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">Taiwania</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
such as transparent explanate margin with honeycomb structure. The 
<typeStatus box="[1272,1370,1869,1894]" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cassida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="juglans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">C. juglans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Solsky" authorityYear="1872" box="[457,571,1905,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cassida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="concha">
<emphasis box="[457,571,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">C. concha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is synonymized with it here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1473,2038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">
The species was recorded only once since is description from 
<collectingCountry box="[894,962,1942,1965]" name="South Korea" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="An, S. L. &amp; Kwon, Y. J. &amp; Lee, S. - M." box="[977,1143,1941,1966]" journalOrPublisher="Insecta Koreana" pageId="7" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 9" part="5" refString="An, S. L., Kwon, Y. J. &amp; Lee, S. - M. (1985) Classification of the leafbeetles from Korea. Part I. Subfamily Hispinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Insecta Koreana, 5, 1 - 9." title="Classification of the leafbeetles from Korea. Part I. Subfamily Hispinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae)" type="journal article" year="1985">
An 
<emphasis box="[1020,1076,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="57">et al.</emphasis>
1985
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Cho, H. W. &amp; Borowiec, L." box="[1163,1436,1941,1966]" journalOrPublisher="Genus" pageId="7" pageNumber="57" pagination="481 - 492" part="25" refString="Cho, H. W. &amp; Borowiec, L. (2014) Three Cassida species new to South Korea, with additional faunistic data and key to all Korean species (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Genus, 25, 481 - 492." title="Three Cassida species new to South Korea, with additional faunistic data and key to all Korean species (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae)" type="journal article" year="2014">Cho &amp; Borowiec (2014)</bibRefCitation>
noted that the record most likely belong to a different species, however, they were not able to locate the original voucher specimen(s).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="8" pageNumber="58">
<bibRefCitation author="Gressitt, J. L." box="[199,370,151,176]" journalOrPublisher="Lignan Natural History Survey and Museum Special Publication" pageId="8" pageNumber="58" pagination="1 - 4" part="5" refString="Gressitt, J. L. (1942) New tortoise beetles from China (Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae). Lignan Natural History Survey and Museum Special Publication, 5, 1 - 4." title="New tortoise beetles from China (Chrysomelidae: Cassidinae)" type="journal article" year="1942">Gressitt (1942)</bibRefCitation>
stated that the 
<typeStatus box="[553,651,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="58">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected on ‘ 
<date box="[869,1027,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="58" value="1936-05-06">May 6, 1936</date>
’ while the specimen bears date 
<date pageId="8" pageNumber="58" value="1936-01-06">6th January 1936</date>
what is probably result of an error as all other characters and data are in accordance with the primary description.
</paragraph>
